        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 20 at 4:51PM EDT by NWS Albany NY</headline>
        <description>At 451 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Becket, or 14 miles southeast of Pittsfield, moving east at 30 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Otis, Monterey, Tyringham, Otis Wood Lanes, Leisure Lee, Algerie Four
Corners, Bonny Rigg Corners, North Otis, Hephzibah Heights, Becket
Center, West Becket, East Otis, Cold Spring, and West Otis.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

A Severe Thunderstorm Watch remains in effect until 900 PM EDT for
western Massachusetts.</instruction>
